photos.caption: A male Vermilion Flycatcher on a bare branch, brilliant scarlet contrasting with dark gray wings.

A Green Jay in close-up portrait, electric blue face with frontal crest, black hood, white crown, bright yellow underparts, and green back.

A Monk Parakeet feeding in a tree canopy among blossoms, green plumage visible from below against sky.
A Black-necked Stilt wading in shallow water, striking black-and-white plumage with long pink legs and needle-like bill.

A Black Phoebe perched on a rusty railing, dark gray-black plumage with white belly and subtle wing bars.
A Eurasian Coot sitting on a mossy log at the water edge, all-black plumage with white bill and frontal shield, lobed toes clearly visible.
A Eurasian Jackdaw perched on a bicycle seat, gray nape, dark plumage, and distinctive pale eye in an urban setting.
A Glossy Ibis wading in shallow water, iridescent dark plumage with green and purple sheen, long curved bill probing the shallows.
A Blue-crowned Parakeet in a tree eating fruit, green plumage with white eye-ring and pale bill visible through branches.
A Blue-crowned Parakeet perched on a wire, green plumage with blue crown, pale eye-ring, and long tail against overcast sky.
An American Kestrel perched on a power line against blue sky, rufous back and tail with dark facial markings visible.
